## Project Overview

A console-based digital attendance management system built in C++ that replaces paper-based attendance taking in lecture halls. The system allows an admin to register students, create lecture sessions, mark and update attendance, generate reports, and export data to CSV files — all stored persistently in text files.

---

## Features

- **Admin Authentication** — Secure login with account creation on first run (3-attempt lockout)
- **Student Management** — Register manually or bulk import from CSV/Excel file
- **Edit & Delete Students** — Changes cascade automatically to all session records
- **Session Management** — Create, edit, and delete lecture sessions with course code, date, time, and duration
- **Attendance Marking** — Mark each student Present or Absent per session
- **Update Attendance** — Correct individual student records after marking
- **Reports** — View attendance list and summary (present count, absent count, attendance rate %)
- **CSV Export** — Export any session report to a `.csv` file openable in Excel or Google Sheets
- **Persistent Storage** — All data saved to text files and reloaded automatically on next run
- **Input Validation** — All inputs validated with cancel (0) option at every prompt
- **Change Password** — Admin can update password from within the system
- **Clear All Data** — Double-confirmed wipe of all records (admin password required)

